title: A School History of the Great War
creator: Albert E. McKinley
description: LibriVox recording of A School History of the Great War, by Albert E. McKinley, Charles A. Coulomb, and Armand J. Gerson. A brief history of The Great War (World War I) designed for students in grades seven and eight. Special emphasis on European history leading up to the war, reasons and events leading to America's eventual entering the war, and possible ramifications of the war for future generations. (Summary by James Christopher) M4B audiobook of complete book For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
